  "quickStartTitle": "Quick Start",
  "quickStartContent": "1. Open the \"Providers\" page.\n2. Select an existing provider or go to \"Custom Provider\".\n3. Fill in the Base URL, API Key, and Model ID.\n4. Tap \"Test Connection\" to verify the configuration.\n5. After testing, tap \"Save\".\n6. Return to the chat page to select the configured model.",
  "providerFieldsTitle": "Provider Configuration Fields",
  "providerNameGuideTitle": "Provider Name",
  "providerNameGuideContent": "Used to distinguish different services. Built-in providers like OpenAI, DeepSeek, and OpenRouter have fixed names. Custom Provider can be named Xiaomi MiMo, company internal model, etc. The name does not affect actual API requests.",
  "baseUrlGuideTitle": "Base URL",
  "baseUrlGuideContent": "Must be the OpenAI-compatible base URL provided by the supplier, and must use HTTPS.\n\nDo not append /chat/completions manually, as KeyChat will add it automatically.\n\nCorrect example:\nhttps://api.example.com/v1\n\nWrong examples:\nhttp://api.example.com/v1\nhttps://api.example.com/v1/chat/completions",
  "apiKeyGuideTitle": "API Key",
  "apiKeyGuideContent": "Created from the corresponding supplier's console. Keys from different suppliers or plans cannot be mixed.\n\nThe key is stored only in the device's secure storage. Do not share the full key with others, and do not include it in screenshots, recordings, or bug reports.\n\nIt is recommended to use a test key with limited quota.",
  "defaultModelGuideTitle": "Default Model",
  "defaultModelGuideContent": "Fill in the model ID actually supported by the supplier. The display name and model ID may differ. Prefer copying the model ID from the supplier's console or official documentation.\n\nIf the connection test does not return a model list, you can manually enter the model ID. Requests will fail if the model does not exist or your account lacks permission.",
  "deepSeekExampleTitle": "DeepSeek Configuration Example",
  "deepSeekApiKeyHint": "Fill in the API Key created on DeepSeek Open Platform",
  "modelNameMayChange": "Model names may change with supplier updates. Please refer to the supplier's console and official documentation.",
  "doNotAppendChatCompletions": "Do not append /chat/completions to the base URL. KeyChat will automatically append the request path.",
  "mimoExampleTitle": "Xiaomi MiMo Configuration Example",
  "mimoRequiresCustomProvider": "The current version does not include a dedicated Xiaomi MiMo provider. Configure it through Custom Provider on the Providers page.",
  "mimoPayAsYouGoTitle": "Pay-as-you-go API",
  "mimoApiKeyHint": "Fill in the pay-as-you-go API Key created on Xiaomi MiMo Open Platform",
  "mimoPayAsYouGoKeyWarning": "Pay-as-you-go API Key and Token Plan API Key cannot be mixed.",
  "mimoTokenPlanTitle": "Token Plan",
  "mimoTokenPlanUrlHint": "Copy the OpenAI-compatible Base URL from Token Plan console",
  "mimoTokenPlanApiKeyHint": "Fill in the dedicated API Key provided by the Token Plan page",
  "mimoTokenPlanWarning": "The base URL and API Key for Token Plan are different from pay-as-you-go API. You must use the address and Key pair provided by the same plan page.",
  "mimoTokenPlanRegionHint": "Different regions may have different Token Plan base URLs. Prefer copying the actual address shown in the console.",
  "mimoOpenAiCompatibleAddressHint": "In KeyChat, select the OpenAI-compatible address. Do not use the Anthropic-compatible address.",
  "mimoCustomProviderNote": "Xiaomi MiMo currently works through Custom Provider. The name you fill in does not affect the request. What actually determines the connection method is the Base URL, API Key, and Model ID.",
  "customProviderGuideTitle": "Custom Provider",
  "customProviderGuideContent": "Custom Provider is suitable for:\n- Xiaomi MiMo\n- Other services compatible with OpenAI Chat Completions\n- User's own HTTPS API gateway\n\nConfiguration requirements:\n- HTTPS Base URL\n- Bearer API Key\n- Model ID\n- Compatible with OpenAI Chat Completions",
  "customProviderCompatibilityWarning": "Different suppliers may vary in model lists, authentication methods, streaming responses, and extended parameters. Being labeled as OpenAI-compatible does not mean all advanced features are fully compatible.",
  "agentGuideTitle": "Agent Introduction",
  "agentGuideContent": "Agent is a set of system prompts that can be saved and reused.\n\nWhen creating an Agent, you can fill in:\n- Name\n- Brief description\n- System prompt",
  "agentGuideExample": "For example:\n\nName: French Learning Assistant\nSystem prompt: You are a patient French teacher. Please explain grammar in Chinese and provide French examples for each knowledge point.\n\nAfter creation, you can select this Agent when starting a new session. Selecting \"No Agent\" will not send additional system prompts.",
  "agentGuideNote": "Agent does not save API Keys and cannot automatically call external tools.",
  "frequentlyAskedQuestionsTitle": "Frequently Asked Questions",
  "noAvailableModelsQuestion": "Why are there no available models?",
  "noAvailableModelsAnswer": "Please check:\n- Is the Provider enabled?\n- Has the API Key been saved?\n- Is the default model filled in?\n- Is the Base URL HTTPS?\n- Is the model ID correct?\n- Is the protocol supported by KeyChat?",
  "connectionTestFailedQuestion": "Why did the connection test fail?",
  "connectionTestFailedAnswer": "Please check:\n- Is the network working?\n- Is the Base URL correct?\n- Does the API Key belong to the current supplier?\n- Has the Key expired?\n- Does the Key match the plan address?\n- Does the supplier support the model list endpoint?\n\nSome compatible services may not provide a model list endpoint. In this case, you can manually enter the model ID, save the configuration, and verify with an actual request.",
  "invalidApiKeyQuestion": "Why does it say the API Key is invalid?",
  "invalidApiKeyAnswer": "Possible reasons:\n- Key entered incorrectly\n- Key has expired\n- Using a Key from the wrong supplier\n- Mixing regular API Key with subscription plan Key\n- Base URL and Key type mismatch",
  "modelAccessDeniedQuestion": "Why does it say I don't have access to the model?",
  "modelAccessDeniedAnswer": "Possible reasons:\n- Model ID may be incorrect\n- Your account doesn't have permission for this model\n- Your plan doesn't include this model\n- The model has been deprecated or renamed",
  "rateLimitQuestion": "Why does it say the request rate is too high?",
  "rateLimitAnswer": "Your account has triggered the supplier's rate limit. Please wait and try again, and check your balance, plan, and concurrency limits.",
  "httpsRequiredQuestion": "Why must HTTPS be used?",
  "httpsRequiredAnswer": "API Keys and message content are sensitive data. HTTPS reduces the risk of data being intercepted or tampered with during transmission, so KeyChat does not allow plain HTTP addresses.",
  "mimoConnectionFailedQuestion": "Why can't I connect after configuring Xiaomi MiMo?",
  "mimoConnectionFailedAnswer": "Please check:\n- Did you select \"Custom Provider\"?\n- Is the Base URL an OpenAI-compatible address?\n- Did you incorrectly append /chat/completions?\n- Are you mixing pay-as-you-go Key with Token Plan Key?\n- Do the Base URL and API Key belong to the same plan?\n- Is the model ID correct?\n- Can your current network access the supplier's service?",
  "mimoNoDedicatedProviderQuestion": "Why is there no dedicated Xiaomi MiMo Provider in settings?",
  "mimoNoDedicatedProviderAnswer": "The current version does not include a built-in Xiaomi MiMo Provider. MiMo provides an OpenAI-compatible API, so it can be configured through \"Custom Provider\". Whether to add a dedicated entry in the future will depend on actual compatibility and testing results.",
  "securityTipsTitle": "Security Tips",
  "securityTipsContent": "- API Keys are stored in the device's secure storage\n- Provider configuration is stored locally\n- Do not use an unlimited quota main account Key\n- It is recommended to create a low-quota test Key\n- Do not share screenshots containing full Keys\n- Clearing app data or uninstalling will delete local configuration\n- KeyChat only allows HTTPS"
}
